# Agent Guardrails

## Protected Paths — Do Not Modify Without Explicit Approval

```
infra/            Infrastructure-as-code (Terraform, Pulumi, CDK)
k8s/              Kubernetes manifests
**/Dockerfile*    Container build definitions
**/.github/       CI/CD workflows
**/migrations/    Database migration files
**/.env*          Environment variable files (never read or log)
**/secrets/       Secrets and credential stores
```

If a task requires changing any of the above, **stop and explain why** before proceeding.
Request explicit confirmation from the user.

## Security Rules

- Never print, log, or embed credentials, tokens, or API keys in code or commit messages.
- Never disable `eslint-disable`, `# noqa`, or similar suppression comments without explaining why.
- Never `--force` push to any branch.
- Never run `DROP`, `TRUNCATE`, or destructive SQL without a safety check.

## Scope Discipline

- Make only changes relevant to the stated task.
- If you discover an unrelated bug, **note it** in your summary but do not fix it in the same PR.
- Do not refactor code that is not related to the task at hand.

## Verification Before Every PR

- [ ] No protected paths modified (or explicit approval obtained)
- [ ] No secrets in diff (`git diff | grep -i 'key\|token\|secret\|password'`)
- [ ] Change is scoped to the task — no unrelated edits
- [ ] All tests pass, lint is clean
